<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n53076c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53076c">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53076c"> 76(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ogham that bothered / Bres</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The first of these is (31) <i>Ogam romesc Bres</i> (&lsquo;<mark>The Ogham which bewildered Bres</mark>&rsquo;). This consists in writing the name of the letter for the letter, as though one should write Alpha-gamma-alpha-mu, etc. for &lsquo;Agamemnon&rsquo;. The name of this cypher is explained by a story to the effect that a message thus concealed was given to the ancient hero called Bres as he was going into battle, and he lost the battle because he was distracted by trying to read it! <small> R.A. Stewart MacAlister, <a name="MSLI" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MSLI"><cite title="source">The Secret Languages of Ireland</cite></a> (Jan 1937) Cryptology, 46-7</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
